{"_type":"issue","id":"pi-extensions-82d","title":"session/resume - Complete state restoration","description":"Implement full ACP session state persistence and restoration.\n\n## Context\nThe ACP extension maintains session state in-memory. This task adds:\n1. Serialize ACP state to pi session files\n2. Restore ACP state on session/resume\n\n## Architecture\n- pi sessions: ~/.pi/agent/sessions/*.jsonl (JSONL format)\n- Config dir: ~/.pi/agent/ (override via PI_CODING_AGENT_DIR)\n- Use SessionManager.appendCustomEntry() for persistence\n\n## Approach\nOn ACP session updates, write custom entries via ctx.sessionManager.appendCustomEntry().\nOn session/resume: read entries, extract ACP state, restore in-memory AcpSession.\n","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"Brendan Shaklovitz","owner":"nyanshak@users.noreply.github.com","created_at":"2026-05-17T05:36:23Z","created_by":"Brendan Shaklovitz","updated_at":"2026-05-17T05:57:49Z","started_at":"2026-05-17T05:46:57Z","closed_at":"2026-05-17T05:57:49Z","close_reason":"Closed","external_ref":"gh/nyanshak/pi-acp#pi-acp-3no","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
